.TH IPOKFS 4
.SH NAME
ipokfs \- `terrorist' IP address file system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aux/ipokfs
[
.B -s
.I service
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Ipokfs
consults
.I ipok
to determine if given IP addresses belong to
countries approved of by the US government,
and caches the answer.
If
.BI /mnt/ipok/ok/ IP
exists,
.I IP
is deemed to be from a non-terrorist country.
.PP
The
.B s
option posts a mountable file descriptor as
.BI /srv/ service.
.SH EXAMPLES
See if
.I ehime
is in a `terrorist' country.
.IP
.EX
% ls /mnt/ipok/ok/135.104.9.17
/mnt/ipok/ok/135.104.9.17
.EE
.SH FILES
.TF /mnt/ipok/ok
.TP
.B /mnt/ipok
mount point for
.I ipokfs
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR ipok (8)
